          "message": "The refactored __getitem__ changes the exception type for a non-file path from KeyError to FileNotFoundError when full_path.is_file() is False, but the else branch is removed. The original code raised KeyError for non-file paths; the new code raises KeyError only if the path does not exist, but if the path exists and is not a file (e.g., a directory), the open() call will fail with IsADirectoryError or PermissionError, not KeyError. This breaks the contract for callers expecting KeyError for any non-file key.",
